Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located in the heart of Brisbane’s thriving western suburbs - DFO Jindalee has transformed into a premium local entertainment, leisure retail and dining hub that delivers a fresh community meeting-place and truly celebrates experiential shopping. 

Areas ranging from 9sqm – 800sqm.

More a collective of premium providores than regular retail – reminisce of James Street and Ferry Road Markets. 

A rare opportunity has arisen for quality artisan operators to join the centres premium fresh food retailer - Amazons Family Fresh Markets. 

On offer are a number of small footprint tenancies ready to go and ideally suited to;

-	Butcher 35m2 (Inc. Cold-room)
-	Salad Bar 15m2
-	Juice Bar 9m2
-	Florist/Plants 9m2

These micro tenancies are ideal for established operators who are seeking to expand their geographical footprint to the burgeoning western suburbs. 

DFO Jindalee attracts visitation from the immediate Centenary suburbs and Brisbane’s West population areas, plus wider visitation from Ipswich, Logan, Beaudesert and the Darling Downs thanks to its strategic positioning and accessibility from fronting the Centenary Highway. This combined population area is predicted to grow to over 1.4million by 2026*, with the immediate trade area population predicted to grow from 520,885 in 2016 to 677,323 by 2026*.

The demographics of the main trade area are characterised by young, high income earners, compared to the wider Brisbane average.

Centre traffic is circa 1Million visitors per annum* with June 2021 visits at 91,963 customers.

Key centre features;

-	Over 800 car parks
-	Large format Gym open from 6am
-	6 Screen Reading Cinema open late daily
-	Eat Street Dining precinct
-	Destination stores include; Nike, Adidas, Asics, BCF & more

For more information please contact CBRE, the exclusive leasing agents.
